sentences: James Emery (born December 21, 1951) is an American jazz guitarist.
In 1973 Emery moved to New York City.
During the 1970s, Emery toured with the Human Arts Ensemble and guests Lester Bowie, George Lewis, and Philip Wilson.
In 1977, he founded the String Trio of New York with violinist Billy Bang and bassist John Lindberg.
He received a Guggenheim Fellowship for music composition in 1995.

At the end of the 1960s, he studied composition and music theory at Cleveland State University.
A few years later, he began taking classical guitar lessons.
During his senior year in high school he taught guitar at a music store run by guitarist Bill DeArango, and during their free time Emery and DeArango played together.
